From georgeh gjhsun George H Subject Re Octopus in Detroit Harold Zazula DLMQC writes I was watching the Detroit Minnesota game last night and thought I saw an octopus on the ice after Ysebaert scored to tie the game at What gives is there some custom to throw octopuses on the ice in Detroit It is a long standing good luck Redwing's tradition to throw an octopus on the ice during a Stanley Cup They say it dates back to ' at the Olympia when the Wings became the team I think to sweep the cup in A lot hardet to throw one from Joe Louis seats than from the old Olympia balcony Funniest I ever saw was when some Tiger fans threw one on the field during a Detroit Toronto baseball game I was living in California and the folks I was watching with had never heard of hockey and were incredulous when I recognized the octopus BEFORE the camera closeup